    {
      "text": "Battle Mania Daiginjō is a 1993 horizontally scrolling shooter developed and published by Vic Tokai for the Mega Drive. It serves as a sequel to the original Battle Mania, which was released in North America under the title Trouble Shooter. Unlike the original Battle Mania, Daginjō was released exclusively for the Japanese and South Korean markets.\nBattle Mania Daiginjō had a limited print run and is consequently one of the most expensive Sega Mega Drive games today.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
